1
00:00:01,088 --> 00:00:03,829
[MELODIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:03,873 --> 00:00:05,918
[WIND WHISTLING]

3
00:01:20,210 --> 00:01:22,386
[WIND WHISTLING]

4
00:01:37,184 --> 00:01:38,185
Ow!

5
00:01:44,626 --> 00:01:46,018
[MAN TALKING ON TV]

6
00:01:46,062 --> 00:01:48,195
KATHERINE: Ooh! Brr!

7
00:01:48,238 --> 00:01:49,935
Hi, Aunt Katherine.

8
00:01:49,979 --> 00:01:51,676
[SIGHS] How are
you, sweetheart?

9
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:52,982
I'm fine.

10
00:01:54,288 --> 00:01:57,595
I know, it's not quite
Christmas as usual,

11
00:01:57,639 --> 00:02:00,424
but we are gonna
have so much fun,
just us girls.

12
00:02:00,468 --> 00:02:02,209
At Grandma's?

13
00:02:02,252 --> 00:02:04,167
Good point.

14
00:02:04,211 --> 00:02:07,605
Probably be forced
to frost precious little
gingerbread man.

15
00:02:07,649 --> 00:02:09,825
Or maybe even stencil
angels on to toilet paper.

16
00:02:09,868 --> 00:02:11,261
What do you think?[GIGGLES]

17
00:02:11,305 --> 00:02:12,958
But at least we'll be
doing it together.

18
00:02:13,002 --> 00:02:14,699
And we'll make it fun,
I promise, okay?

19
00:02:14,743 --> 00:02:15,831
Okay.

20
00:02:15,874 --> 00:02:17,441
All right, so
where's your Mom?

21
00:02:17,485 --> 00:02:19,182
Kitchen.Okay.

22
00:02:21,097 --> 00:02:23,099
Maddie?

23
00:02:23,143 --> 00:02:24,927
MAN ON TV: ...and around 
the greater Minneapolis, 
St. Paul area.

24
00:02:24,970 --> 00:02:27,582
KATHERINE: Princess! Now take a look at the way...

25
00:02:30,933 --> 00:02:32,021
KATHERINE: Hey, Maddie?

26
00:02:32,064 --> 00:02:33,196
[GROANING]

27
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:34,197
Hello?

28
00:02:35,416 --> 00:02:37,505
Merry Christmas
to you too.

29
00:02:37,548 --> 00:02:38,636
Hi.

30
00:02:39,681 --> 00:02:40,769
What's this?

31
00:02:40,812 --> 00:02:42,118
What does it look like?

32
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:45,077
A petition for divorce.
I just signed it.

33
00:02:45,121 --> 00:02:46,688
Oh, Maddie.

34
00:02:46,731 --> 00:02:49,212
Somehow, Christmas eve
doesn't seem like the day

35
00:02:49,256 --> 00:02:51,736
for man to put asunder
what God hath joined.

36
00:02:51,780 --> 00:02:54,826
Well, maybe you can
think of a better day.
How about next week,

37
00:02:54,870 --> 00:02:55,914
on New Year's Day?

38
00:02:55,958 --> 00:02:58,090
Or next month
on my birthday.

39
00:02:58,134 --> 00:02:59,918
Or the month after that

40
00:02:59,962 --> 00:03:02,051
on what was supposed to
be the 15th anniversary
of our wedding?

41
00:03:02,094 --> 00:03:04,532
Yes, yes, it's all right to
feel sorry for yourself.

42
00:03:04,575 --> 00:03:06,142
Matt did you wrong.

43
00:03:06,186 --> 00:03:09,232
But your daughters
are entitled to
a merry Christmas.

44
00:03:09,841 --> 00:03:10,886
You're right.

45
00:03:10,929 --> 00:03:12,192
Good.

46
00:03:12,235 --> 00:03:14,106
So come one, snow's
piling up, let's go.

47
00:03:15,151 --> 00:03:16,805
I like snow on Christmas.

48
00:03:16,848 --> 00:03:18,720
Make everything look new.

49
00:03:18,763 --> 00:03:23,464
Yeah. Well, Mother Nature's
makeover is making driving
a bitch, so come on.

50
00:03:23,507 --> 00:03:26,206
Let's go. Out, out, out.

51
00:03:28,251 --> 00:03:30,427
MADDIE: Kirby, let's go.

52
00:03:30,471 --> 00:03:31,907
You ready, honey?Yeah.

53
00:03:31,950 --> 00:03:32,995
What are you reading?

54
00:03:33,038 --> 00:03:34,649
Back Lash.

55
00:03:34,692 --> 00:03:36,955
Ah, I was gonna give you
a copy of that for
your 13th birthday.

56
00:03:36,999 --> 00:03:38,261
Good girl.

57
00:03:38,305 --> 00:03:40,045
Dad bought it
for me last week.

58
00:03:40,089 --> 00:03:42,744
He said it's a good account of
how women get jerked around.

59
00:03:43,962 --> 00:03:46,138
Have you read it, Mom?Mm-hm.

60
00:03:46,182 --> 00:03:47,183
What do you think?

61
00:03:48,837 --> 00:03:51,143
I think your father knows
what he's talking about.

62
00:03:52,623 --> 00:03:53,972
Kirby, come on!

63
00:03:54,016 --> 00:03:55,235
KIRBY: I'm coming.

64
00:03:55,278 --> 00:03:57,237
Come on, girls.

65
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:58,890
[WIND HOWLING]

66
00:03:58,934 --> 00:04:00,327
[DOG BARKING]

67
00:04:02,633 --> 00:04:05,332
Kirby, Ellie,
careful, it's slippery.

68
00:04:06,594 --> 00:04:08,422
Brr! It's cold!

69
00:04:08,465 --> 00:04:10,075
Did anybody turn
the heat off?

70
00:04:10,119 --> 00:04:12,252
Dad always does that.

71
00:04:12,295 --> 00:04:15,124
Okay, well, then,
go on, I'll be right back.

72
00:04:22,610 --> 00:04:24,525
[MELLOW PIANO MUSIC PLAYING]

73
00:04:31,532 --> 00:04:33,011
[SIGHS]

74
00:05:26,021 --> 00:05:27,892
Merry Christmas, Matt.

75
00:05:47,956 --> 00:05:49,827
[WIND HOWLING]

76
00:05:59,010 --> 00:06:02,492
WOMAN: [OVER PA SYSTEM] 
MSP passenger, Rene Shaw, 
please report to gate number...

77
00:06:02,536 --> 00:06:04,233
I apologize for the delay.

78
00:06:04,276 --> 00:06:07,932
Sir, you'll have to get in line
down there. They'll process you.

79
00:06:07,976 --> 00:06:09,543
We appreciate
your patience.

80
00:06:09,586 --> 00:06:11,458
Trust me, we'll get you
on your flights.

81
00:06:11,501 --> 00:06:13,503
Everyone will get to
where they need to go.

82
00:06:13,547 --> 00:06:14,548
Hello.

83
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:16,463
Here we go.

84
00:06:20,031 --> 00:06:21,424
Excuse me, ma'am?Yes.

85
00:06:21,468 --> 00:06:24,166
Is flight 118 to Chicago
leaving on time?

86
00:06:24,209 --> 00:06:27,691
Well, I'm sorry, the airport
plows are working
as fast as they can,

87
00:06:27,735 --> 00:06:30,825
but we are down
to one runway
and that means delays.

88
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:33,131
How long?

89
00:06:33,175 --> 00:06:35,612
Well, we're looking
at two hours,
maybe three on all departures.

90
00:06:35,656 --> 00:06:36,787
[SIGHS]

91
00:06:36,831 --> 00:06:38,876
Oh, we could practically
drive to Chicago.

92
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:40,574
Look on the bright side.

93
00:06:40,617 --> 00:06:43,359
It means two more hours
of junk food
and crossword puzzles

94
00:06:43,403 --> 00:06:45,056
before we get to Grandma's.

95
00:06:45,100 --> 00:06:47,450
We'll post new
flight times
as soon as possible

96
00:06:47,494 --> 00:06:50,453
and we're offering
complimentary coffee
in our VIP lounge

97
00:06:50,497 --> 00:06:51,976
for all our travelers.Thank you.

98
00:06:52,020 --> 00:06:53,325
Thank you for
your patience.

99
00:06:53,369 --> 00:06:54,631
Okay.
Can I help you, sir?

100
00:06:58,418 --> 00:07:00,637
KATHERINE: Decisions, decisions.

101
00:07:03,335 --> 00:07:07,601
Hey, Maddie, here's
some news we can use.

102
00:07:07,644 --> 00:07:10,691
"Cosmetic surgeries
you can do over lunch."

103
00:07:10,734 --> 00:07:14,129
"Wrinkles... Must you
look like your mother?"

104
00:07:14,172 --> 00:07:16,958
"Orgasms, on your own.
Guaranteed."

105
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:22,354
Guess we don't need
you guys anymore.

106
00:07:24,269 --> 00:07:27,316
Okay, I'll stick to
the smart money.

107
00:07:27,359 --> 00:07:30,188
What did you think of
Mother's latest?

108
00:07:30,232 --> 00:07:33,453
[SIGHS] She sent me a copy.
But I haven't read it.

109
00:07:33,496 --> 00:07:34,802
Neither have I.

110
00:07:34,845 --> 00:07:36,412
Come on, eight volumes?

111
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:39,589
My law degree barely
required that much reading.

112
00:07:39,633 --> 00:07:42,157
I wonder if Dad reads.

113
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:45,334
I don't know,
but I'm sure if he did

114
00:07:45,377 --> 00:07:47,902
he'd say that Mother
left out a few chapters.

115
00:07:47,945 --> 00:07:50,992
Like, "Tend your marriage
as well as your garden"?

116
00:07:51,035 --> 00:07:52,820
Why do we always
blame Mother?

117
00:07:52,863 --> 00:07:55,518
I mean, Dad is the one
who had the affair.

118
00:07:55,562 --> 00:07:57,259
'Cause she drove him to it.

119
00:07:57,302 --> 00:08:00,044
Hen-pecking wasn't
his idea of foreplay.

120
00:08:00,088 --> 00:08:02,177
She made him do it? Come on!

121
00:08:02,220 --> 00:08:03,526
That's right.

122
00:08:03,570 --> 00:08:05,833
Since when are you an expert
on marriage anyway?

123
00:08:05,876 --> 00:08:09,140
You can't commit to
a bowl of goldfish.

124
00:08:09,184 --> 00:08:11,316
This thing with Matt is
not gonna turn into

125
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:14,319
some bonding thing between
you and Mom, is it?

126
00:08:16,147 --> 00:08:17,453
Hey, Mom.

127
00:08:17,497 --> 00:08:19,977
Hey, sweetie.
Let's go pay for this.

128
00:08:23,938 --> 00:08:26,331
Mom, when are we
gonna call Dad?

129
00:08:26,375 --> 00:08:28,464
What if we're flying
when we said we'd call?

130
00:08:28,508 --> 00:08:31,162
Oh, don't worry, sweetheart.
We'll get hold of him.

131
00:08:31,206 --> 00:08:34,862
Did he tell you girls
that he was flying down
to Miami this morning?

132
00:08:34,905 --> 00:08:36,777
I think so.

133
00:08:36,820 --> 00:08:39,257
Pretty strange way to
spend Christmas, huh?

134
00:08:39,301 --> 00:08:42,434
Daddy's probably sitting on
Grandpa Hill's patio right now

135
00:08:42,478 --> 00:08:45,612
and getting a sunburn.

136
00:08:45,655 --> 00:08:49,616
I wish we could spend
Christmas at our house
like we always do.

137
00:08:50,704 --> 00:08:51,792
I know.

138
00:08:51,835 --> 00:08:53,358
CASHIER: Your change.Thank you.

139
00:08:53,402 --> 00:08:54,534
Have a merry Christmas.

140
00:08:54,577 --> 00:08:56,884
You too.

141
00:08:56,927 --> 00:08:59,669
KATHERINE: We know 
there is no such thing 
as a civil divorce.

142
00:08:59,713 --> 00:09:01,715
It's a lie and an oxymoron.

143
00:09:01,758 --> 00:09:03,847
MADDIE: Like,
"happily married?"

144
00:09:03,891 --> 00:09:05,849
Look, I can be gracious
about this.

145
00:09:05,893 --> 00:09:09,549
He can have his clothes,
his golf clubs, definitely
his pile of sneakers.

146
00:09:09,592 --> 00:09:11,638
[METAL DETECTOR BEEPS]

147
00:09:11,681 --> 00:09:13,378
But I'm serious.

148
00:09:13,422 --> 00:09:15,642
In a few months,
after some lawyer
trains you like a pitbull,

149
00:09:15,685 --> 00:09:17,644
you'll draw blood
over the toaster.

150
00:09:17,687 --> 00:09:19,254
Well, it is a poor slicer.

151
00:09:20,168 --> 00:09:21,735
[METAL DETECTOR BEEPS]

152
00:09:23,345 --> 00:09:24,564
Jewelry?

153
00:09:28,132 --> 00:09:29,177
And the ring.

154
00:09:29,220 --> 00:09:31,483
Oh... uh... this
ain't coming off.

155
00:09:31,527 --> 00:09:34,965
Ma'am, this is a metal detector
and I can't let you go anywhere
until it stops beeping.

156
00:09:35,009 --> 00:09:36,445
Look, I'm not trying
to be contrary,

157
00:09:36,488 --> 00:09:37,881
but I'm telling you,
it won't come off.

158
00:09:37,925 --> 00:09:39,013
It's like a barnacle.

159
00:09:39,056 --> 00:09:40,362
Ma'am, please.

160
00:09:43,583 --> 00:09:44,671
[RING CLATTERS]

161
00:09:44,714 --> 00:09:46,020
Thank you.

162
00:09:46,063 --> 00:09:48,065
The cold weather, Maddie,
it shrinks pinkies.

163
00:09:48,109 --> 00:09:50,546
If only it did
the same for hips.

164
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:51,634
[METAL DETECTOR BEEPING]

165
00:09:51,678 --> 00:09:53,723
[PEOPLE GROANING]

166
00:09:53,767 --> 00:09:55,116
MAN: Come on, lady!

167
00:09:55,725 --> 00:09:57,771
Okay, okay. Relax.

168
00:09:57,814 --> 00:09:59,381
[METAL DETECTOR BEEPS]

169
00:09:59,424 --> 00:10:00,991
Do you have anything
in your hair?

170
00:10:01,035 --> 00:10:03,080
What, like a grenade?

171
00:10:03,124 --> 00:10:04,691
Like a barrette?

172
00:10:05,169 --> 00:10:06,257
Oh.

173
00:10:06,997 --> 00:10:08,042
Sorry.

174
00:10:12,263 --> 00:10:14,004
[PEOPLE CHEERING]

175
00:10:19,662 --> 00:10:21,272
Thanks.Mm-hm.

176
00:10:39,639 --> 00:10:41,641
What do you
girls wanna eat?

177
00:10:41,684 --> 00:10:43,077
Um... yogurt.

178
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,165
French fries.

179
00:10:44,208 --> 00:10:45,688
How about you, Kat?

180
00:10:45,732 --> 00:10:48,343
Before we get to Mom's,
I want to eat
any and everything

181
00:10:48,386 --> 00:10:49,953
that's bad for me.[GIRLS GIGGLING]

182
00:10:49,997 --> 00:10:51,128
I'm game if you are.

183
00:10:51,172 --> 00:10:55,698
Quesadillas,
corn dogs,
chili fries.

184
00:10:55,742 --> 00:11:00,137
Ooh. Double chocolate
marshmallow cone with sprinkles.

185
00:11:00,181 --> 00:11:01,965
[GIRLS EXCLAIM]

186
00:11:02,662 --> 00:11:04,098
BOTH: Dad!

187
00:11:04,141 --> 00:11:09,233
Hey, Kirby! Hold on,
I'll be right there!
Excuse me.

188
00:11:09,277 --> 00:11:10,626
What's Dad
doing here?

189
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:12,106
I thought
he was leaving.

190
00:11:12,149 --> 00:11:14,151
Matt looks good.
That trench gives him

191
00:11:14,195 --> 00:11:16,501
this sort of rugged
war correspondent look.

192
00:11:16,545 --> 00:11:18,373
Katherine, shut up.

193
00:11:18,416 --> 00:11:20,418
He looks like
a typical sportswriter.

194
00:11:20,462 --> 00:11:23,073
I gave him that
because I was sick of
his hooded sweatshirt.

195
00:11:23,117 --> 00:11:24,901
What's he doing here?KIRBY: Come on, Dad. Hurry!

196
00:11:24,945 --> 00:11:27,208
Let's see...
Airport? Holiday?

197
00:11:27,251 --> 00:11:28,731
Trying to
catch a plane?

198
00:11:28,775 --> 00:11:30,254
Hi, sweet peas!

199
00:11:30,298 --> 00:11:31,429
Daddy!

200
00:11:32,343 --> 00:11:33,736
Hi, pumpkin.

201
00:11:35,172 --> 00:11:36,521
You smell like Christmas.

202
00:11:36,565 --> 00:11:38,001
I thought you went
to Grandpa's.

203
00:11:38,045 --> 00:11:39,829
I am. Just
a little while.

204
00:11:42,136 --> 00:11:43,224
Hi, Katherine.

205
00:11:44,312 --> 00:11:45,487
Merry Christmas to you.

206
00:11:45,530 --> 00:11:47,358
Same to you, stranger.

207
00:11:47,402 --> 00:11:49,883
Boy, you really
screw things up.

208
00:11:53,277 --> 00:11:55,758
Hello, Maddie.
You look good.

209
00:11:55,802 --> 00:11:57,412
What are you
doing here?

210
00:11:57,455 --> 00:11:59,936
I'm killing time,
I was supposed to catch
a flight this morning,

211
00:11:59,980 --> 00:12:01,633
but didn't finish
my column till noon,

212
00:12:01,677 --> 00:12:04,767
so ran up a cab out here
just in time to see
the "delayed" signs

213
00:12:04,811 --> 00:12:06,943
lighting up the boards.

214
00:12:06,987 --> 00:12:08,684
Oh, well, now that
you two are here...

215
00:12:08,728 --> 00:12:10,207
[GIRLS GIGGLE]

216
00:12:10,251 --> 00:12:13,167
...I don't care
if we're snowed in
all night long.

217
00:12:13,210 --> 00:12:14,777
Well, you know
we're on our way to Mother's,

218
00:12:14,821 --> 00:12:18,085
and I'm sure your flight
is probably gonna leave
any time now,

219
00:12:18,128 --> 00:12:20,304
so, girls, say goodbye
to your father.

220
00:12:20,348 --> 00:12:22,045
Mom, Dad can
eat with us!

221
00:12:22,089 --> 00:12:23,568
Dad, you're hungry,
aren't you?

222
00:12:23,612 --> 00:12:25,570
I'm starving.
I'm just starved.

223
00:12:25,614 --> 00:12:26,658
[KISSES]

224
00:12:26,702 --> 00:12:28,356
It's okay,
I've got plenty of time.

225
00:12:28,399 --> 00:12:30,532
My flight doesn't leave
for an hour and a half.

226
00:12:30,575 --> 00:12:32,795
Oh, well, great,
uh... then...

227
00:12:32,839 --> 00:12:36,320
Why don't you and Kat go on to
the restaurant, and I'll take
the girls to the restroom.

228
00:12:36,364 --> 00:12:37,408
Okay?

229
00:12:40,194 --> 00:12:41,804
Matt, what were
you thinking?

230
00:12:41,848 --> 00:12:43,937
I wasn't.
Obviously.

231
00:12:43,980 --> 00:12:45,895
Excuse me.

232
00:12:45,939 --> 00:12:49,246
I just can't believe
that you threw it
all away like that.

233
00:12:49,290 --> 00:12:50,944
[SIGHS]

234
00:12:50,987 --> 00:12:51,988
I know.

235
00:12:53,511 --> 00:12:55,209
I know.

236
00:12:55,252 --> 00:12:57,820
Well, I for one,
am gonna miss you a lot.

237
00:12:57,864 --> 00:13:00,562
I mean, even though
I'm really angry with you,

238
00:13:00,605 --> 00:13:02,259
I still love you.

239
00:13:02,303 --> 00:13:04,044
Thanks.

240
00:13:04,087 --> 00:13:06,176
How are you holding up?

241
00:13:06,220 --> 00:13:08,265
Ah... Not good.

242
00:13:08,309 --> 00:13:13,531
The thought of
not coming home to Maddie
and the girls ever again.

243
00:13:13,575 --> 00:13:16,796
I don't want my girls
growing up
in a broken home.

244
00:13:19,146 --> 00:13:20,669
So how's Maddie?

245
00:13:20,712 --> 00:13:22,932
You know Maddie,
she'll be fine.

246
00:13:22,976 --> 00:13:25,500
Few days,
she'll forget all about you.

247
00:13:28,851 --> 00:13:30,157
I'm joking.

248
00:13:32,159 --> 00:13:35,075
Matt, come on. Let's go
get something to eat, okay?

249
00:13:36,032 --> 00:13:37,729
All right? Come on.

250
00:13:42,125 --> 00:13:43,170
Kirby!

251
00:13:43,213 --> 00:13:44,693
KIRBY: Daddy!

252
00:13:48,436 --> 00:13:50,003
Thanks for
my Christmas present, Dad.

253
00:13:50,046 --> 00:13:51,482
It was exactly
what I wanted.

254
00:13:51,526 --> 00:13:53,571
Oh, you're welcome,
sweetheart. I love you.

255
00:13:53,615 --> 00:13:55,835
[GASPS]
What did you get?

256
00:13:55,878 --> 00:13:58,054
Dad bought me
a charm bracelet.

257
00:13:58,098 --> 00:14:01,449
Oh, that is so pretty.
Good work, Dad.

258
00:14:01,492 --> 00:14:04,104
KIRBY: I got a Vikings helmet
signed by...

259
00:14:04,626 --> 00:14:06,193
Randall...

260
00:14:06,236 --> 00:14:08,021
Cunningham!

261
00:14:08,064 --> 00:14:09,892
And a brand-new
catcher's mask.

262
00:14:09,936 --> 00:14:12,895
KATHERINE: Oh, that's cool!

263
00:14:12,939 --> 00:14:14,941
I ordered quesadillas
and French fries for the girls.

264
00:14:14,984 --> 00:14:16,377
Good.

265
00:14:16,420 --> 00:14:18,640
KIRBY: Are you gonna take me
to spring training or not?

266
00:14:18,683 --> 00:14:22,470
You said you would,
but Mom said
I'd miss too much school.

267
00:14:22,513 --> 00:14:24,472
You know what?

268
00:14:24,515 --> 00:14:27,431
Baseball season is
a long ways off.

269
00:14:27,475 --> 00:14:29,216
I'll talk this over with
your mom later, okay?

270
00:14:29,259 --> 00:14:31,044
KIRBY: Okay.

271
00:14:31,087 --> 00:14:33,220
I never should have let
your father name you
after Kirby Puckett.

272
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:37,615
Good thing your Dad's
not a Yankees fan.

273
00:14:37,659 --> 00:14:39,791
You could have been named
after Catfish Hunter.

274
00:14:39,835 --> 00:14:43,883
Yeah. How's
my little Catfish?

275
00:14:43,926 --> 00:14:46,233
Mommy!
He's tickling me.

276
00:14:53,066 --> 00:14:55,459
Why don't you
sit down, honey?
Let's eat up.

277
00:14:55,503 --> 00:14:57,113
Daddy's plane
is leaving soon.

278
00:14:57,157 --> 00:14:59,159
We'll walk him
to the gate.

279
00:15:00,377 --> 00:15:04,599
Mom, Dad, since
you're both here...

280
00:15:04,642 --> 00:15:09,125
I mean, I wasn't really sure
when we'd all be together again,

281
00:15:09,169 --> 00:15:13,086
so I'd like to give you
your Christmas present now.

282
00:15:18,439 --> 00:15:19,570
Open it now?

283
00:15:19,614 --> 00:15:20,615
Yeah.

284
00:15:25,750 --> 00:15:27,970
I'm taking it to
Grandma Parker's.

285
00:15:28,014 --> 00:15:30,799
She's gonna help me
decorate a cover for it.

286
00:15:30,842 --> 00:15:32,627
It's a photo album.

287
00:15:32,670 --> 00:15:36,196
Oh, yeah, this is terrific.

288
00:15:37,545 --> 00:15:40,504
Oh, Ellie, this is
a great gift, thank you.

289
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:42,942
Let me see.

290
00:15:47,424 --> 00:15:48,556
Where'd you get these?

291
00:15:48,599 --> 00:15:51,733
Up in the attic.
They were in some boxes.

292
00:15:51,776 --> 00:15:55,041
Ellie, I really wish
you wouldn't go
through those boxes.

293
00:15:55,084 --> 00:15:56,956
They're personal.

294
00:15:56,999 --> 00:16:00,046
I mean, you wouldn't
want me rifling through
your stuff, would you?

295
00:16:00,089 --> 00:16:02,483
What, she can't look at her
parents' wedding pictures?

296
00:16:03,571 --> 00:16:05,007
What's the point?

297
00:16:07,096 --> 00:16:09,620
I'll be back in a few minutes.

298
00:16:09,664 --> 00:16:11,796
Don't you have a plane
to catch, Matt?

299
00:16:15,844 --> 00:16:18,760
Ellie, this is a wonderful
present, sweetheart.

300
00:16:18,803 --> 00:16:21,154
I can't wait to see
how you're gonna decorate it.

301
00:16:23,330 --> 00:16:24,635
I'll be right back, okay?

302
00:16:24,679 --> 00:16:26,681
Could you watch the girls
for a minute?

303
00:16:28,335 --> 00:16:30,554
WOMAN: [OVER PA SYSTEM] 
All passengers,

304
00:16:30,598 --> 00:16:33,079
please do not 
leave your bags unattended.

305
00:16:34,167 --> 00:16:36,038
MATT: Hey.

306
00:16:36,082 --> 00:16:39,172
So you're not feeling nostalgic.
Why take it out on her?

307
00:16:39,215 --> 00:16:42,653
I'm surprised you didn't cut
me out the photos before
you stuck them in the attic.

308
00:16:42,697 --> 00:16:44,264
Don't you turn this on me.

309
00:16:44,307 --> 00:16:46,440
If Ellie wants to
document our relationship,

310
00:16:46,483 --> 00:16:48,224
then she'd better include
a picture of her father

311
00:16:48,268 --> 00:16:49,878
and the tart that
he took up with.

312
00:16:49,921 --> 00:16:52,228
I never took up
with anybody.
I made a mistake.

313
00:16:52,272 --> 00:16:53,795
A mistake?Yes.

314
00:16:53,838 --> 00:16:55,971
A mistake is spelling
some jock's name wrong
in your column

315
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:58,060
and then printing
a correction the next day.

316
00:16:58,104 --> 00:17:00,367
It was one stupid night.
I never even planned it.

317
00:17:00,410 --> 00:17:01,759
So let me get this straight.

318
00:17:01,803 --> 00:17:04,110
I am home,
cleaning house,
feeding the girls,

319
00:17:04,153 --> 00:17:07,374
and by the way, trying to keep
my writing career going to
help pay the mortgage,

320
00:17:07,417 --> 00:17:10,768
and you're just on the road
with a football team,
writing a few columns

321
00:17:10,812 --> 00:17:13,510
and oops! Falling in bed
with the team's PR girl.

322
00:17:13,554 --> 00:17:15,077
That's not exactly
what happened.

323
00:17:15,121 --> 00:17:17,123
I don't want to know
exactly what happened

324
00:17:17,166 --> 00:17:19,690
because I don't want to spend
one more second thinking
about how you did it.

325
00:17:19,734 --> 00:17:23,607
Just... Maddie,
please, just...
Will you sit down?

326
00:17:25,653 --> 00:17:26,828
[SIGHS]

327
00:17:26,871 --> 00:17:28,960
[SOFT, PLEASANT MUSIC PLAYING]

328
00:17:35,445 --> 00:17:37,273
Maddie, I'm sorry.

329
00:17:38,231 --> 00:17:40,059
I'm so sorry.

330
00:17:46,369 --> 00:17:48,763
I wish there was
something I could...

331
00:17:56,249 --> 00:17:58,425
I signed
the divorce papers today.

332
00:18:00,166 --> 00:18:03,299
Our process server
will be coming by
your office next week.

333
00:18:05,301 --> 00:18:07,390
Sorry to spoil
the surprise.

334
00:18:09,436 --> 00:18:11,612
I won't be there.

335
00:18:11,655 --> 00:18:13,570
Let me guess,
taking another road trip?

336
00:18:13,614 --> 00:18:16,921
No, taking another job.

337
00:18:16,965 --> 00:18:19,141
What do you mean?

338
00:18:19,185 --> 00:18:21,056
I'm flying to
Connecticut on Monday,

339
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:23,667
straight from
my dad's place.

340
00:18:23,711 --> 00:18:26,627
That's why I'm wearing
my one good coat.

341
00:18:26,670 --> 00:18:27,845
Connecticut?

342
00:18:29,064 --> 00:18:30,587
It's with
the All Sports channel.

343
00:18:30,631 --> 00:18:32,328
Hosting a new show.

344
00:18:32,372 --> 00:18:34,504
They called me
a few weeks ago,

345
00:18:34,548 --> 00:18:37,028
I did an audition tape,

346
00:18:37,072 --> 00:18:39,553
things moved fairly
quickly after that.

347
00:18:39,596 --> 00:18:42,556
It's the best offer
I've ever had.

348
00:18:42,599 --> 00:18:44,471
You mean,
you're leaving for good?

349
00:18:44,514 --> 00:18:46,168
What difference
does it make to you?

350
00:18:46,212 --> 00:18:48,518
For the past two months,
you've made it perfectly clear

351
00:18:48,562 --> 00:18:49,998
you never want
to see me again.

352
00:18:50,041 --> 00:18:51,565
You haven't even
discussed this with me.

353
00:18:51,608 --> 00:18:54,002
You never returned
any of my phone calls.

354
00:18:54,045 --> 00:18:55,917
What about the girls?

355
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:58,093
I'll see them
on the weekends,

356
00:18:58,137 --> 00:18:59,964
which, under your terms,

357
00:19:00,008 --> 00:19:03,054
is pretty much when
I get to see them
regardless of where I live.

358
00:19:03,098 --> 00:19:05,753
And just when
were you planning on
telling me this?

359
00:19:05,796 --> 00:19:08,364
Right after the holidays.

360
00:19:08,408 --> 00:19:10,758
When did you plan
on telling me
you filed for divorce?

361
00:19:13,587 --> 00:19:15,241
[SIGHS]Hill?

362
00:19:15,284 --> 00:19:16,677
Hill?

363
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:18,331
MATT: Mr. Vickery.

364
00:19:18,374 --> 00:19:22,204
Good afternoon.
Happy holidays.

365
00:19:22,248 --> 00:19:25,251
Speaking of facts, Hill,
you got one wrong in
that column of yours.

366
00:19:25,294 --> 00:19:27,427
I never said
I was interested
in selling my team.

367
00:19:27,470 --> 00:19:29,429
I don't know where
you got that idea.

368
00:19:29,472 --> 00:19:30,995
You write it again,
I'll see you in court.

369
00:19:31,039 --> 00:19:32,649
What, you think
he just made it up?

370
00:19:32,693 --> 00:19:34,173
He quoted two different sources.

371
00:19:37,611 --> 00:19:40,048
Didn't think
you still read me.

372
00:19:40,091 --> 00:19:41,267
You're married to him?

373
00:19:41,789 --> 00:19:43,878
Technically.

374
00:19:43,921 --> 00:19:47,186
By technically,
I mean we don't have
a court date yet.

375
00:19:47,229 --> 00:19:48,274
We're separated.

376
00:19:48,317 --> 00:19:49,318
We're history.

377
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:53,844
Oh.

378
00:19:53,888 --> 00:19:56,325
Merry Christmas
to both of you.

379
00:19:56,369 --> 00:19:57,979
And happy new year.

380
00:19:58,022 --> 00:19:59,894
Happy new year.

381
00:20:03,158 --> 00:20:05,334
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

382
00:20:12,385 --> 00:20:14,909
Just remember,

383
00:20:14,952 --> 00:20:17,303
you're the one
who wanted to end it.

384
00:20:17,346 --> 00:20:19,218
Not me.

385
00:20:19,261 --> 00:20:21,872
Oh, no, Matt.
You ended it.

386
00:20:21,916 --> 00:20:23,831
I just handled the paperwork.

387
00:20:34,885 --> 00:20:36,278
Boarding pass, please.

388
00:20:37,758 --> 00:20:39,107
Have a nice trip.

389
00:20:40,543 --> 00:20:42,806
I'll be back
in a few days.

390
00:20:42,850 --> 00:20:44,286
How many days?

391
00:20:44,330 --> 00:20:47,028
Uh... six days.

392
00:20:47,071 --> 00:20:50,118
Remember, we're gonna
have Christmas all over again
at my apartment.

393
00:20:51,119 --> 00:20:53,121
Oh,

394
00:20:53,164 --> 00:20:55,428
maybe you can bring
some decorations from Earl's.

395
00:20:55,471 --> 00:20:59,040
I got a tree,
and I got presents.

396
00:20:59,083 --> 00:21:01,172
But we need decorations.

397
00:21:01,216 --> 00:21:04,524
Well, make sure you bring
your Christmas stockings.
Mine too.

398
00:21:04,567 --> 00:21:08,484
Dad, you don't
have a fireplace
to hang 'em on.

399
00:21:08,528 --> 00:21:12,053
Well, we'll hang them from...
We'll tack 'em to the wall.

400
00:21:14,360 --> 00:21:17,101
Is this how
we're gonna spend Christmas
from now on?

401
00:21:23,804 --> 00:21:25,632
You know what?

402
00:21:25,675 --> 00:21:27,895
Let's talk about things
when I get back, all right?

403
00:21:27,938 --> 00:21:30,245
Okay.

404
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:32,639
...passengers should be 
on board at this time.

405
00:21:34,249 --> 00:21:35,990
Well, it's time
for Dad to go.

406
00:21:37,383 --> 00:21:38,819
ELLIE: Tell Grandpa Bill
I miss him.

407
00:21:38,862 --> 00:21:40,299
MATT: I will.KIRBY: Me too.

408
00:21:41,952 --> 00:21:43,040
Bye, Dad.

409
00:21:43,084 --> 00:21:44,172
Bye.

410
00:21:45,391 --> 00:21:46,609
Merry Christmas, Katherine.

411
00:21:47,044 --> 00:21:48,437
You too.

412
00:21:49,525 --> 00:21:50,613
Merry Christmas, Maddie.

413
00:22:02,712 --> 00:22:04,453
Boarding pass, sir.

414
00:22:04,497 --> 00:22:06,716
Thank you, there you go.

415
00:22:14,202 --> 00:22:15,334
Hello.

416
00:22:21,514 --> 00:22:23,820
Hey, girls, penny
for your thoughts.

417
00:22:26,214 --> 00:22:28,695
Okay, how about
five dollars?

418
00:22:28,738 --> 00:22:31,045
I don't wanna talk
about it, Mom.

419
00:22:32,089 --> 00:22:33,526
Me neither.

420
00:22:35,354 --> 00:22:39,401
Look, I know
it's not fair,
and I'm sorry.

421
00:22:39,445 --> 00:22:43,666
Do you know what,
every family goes through
something at some time.

422
00:22:43,710 --> 00:22:46,669
And in time, everything
will work itself out.

423
00:22:46,713 --> 00:22:48,236
You'll see.

424
00:22:48,279 --> 00:22:50,064
But for now, it's just us girls.

425
00:22:50,107 --> 00:22:52,196
So what do you say
we make the best of it, huh?

426
00:22:52,893 --> 00:22:54,634
Kirby?Okay.

427
00:22:54,677 --> 00:22:56,766
Ellie?All right.

428
00:22:56,810 --> 00:22:59,813
WOMAN: [OVER PA SYSTEM] 
Flight number 1312 
to Denver has been delayed.

429
00:22:59,856 --> 00:23:02,598
Please check the screens 
for further updates.

430
00:23:02,642 --> 00:23:03,947
And Katherine?

431
00:23:04,992 --> 00:23:06,689
You betcha, hon.

432
00:23:08,430 --> 00:23:10,737
That was very diplomatic
of you.

433
00:23:10,780 --> 00:23:12,434
And sensitive.

434
00:23:12,478 --> 00:23:14,305
For a moment there,
you almost had me convinced

435
00:23:14,349 --> 00:23:17,134
that you didn't grow up with
the same mother as I did.

436
00:23:21,835 --> 00:23:24,490
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

437
00:23:26,492 --> 00:23:27,667
Hello.

438
00:23:27,710 --> 00:23:29,930
Hello, Mother.
Merry Christmas.

439
00:23:29,973 --> 00:23:32,236
Merry Christmas.
Hold on a minute, dear.

440
00:23:40,767 --> 00:23:42,769
There! Finito!

441
00:23:44,510 --> 00:23:46,729
I just finished
rolling my last candle

442
00:23:46,773 --> 00:23:50,429
made from the beeswax
of my first colony
of honeybees.

443
00:23:50,472 --> 00:23:54,171
Now we're all gonna be bathed
in beautiful candlelight.

444
00:23:54,215 --> 00:23:57,479
Well, it sounds nice,
but I have some bad news.

445
00:23:57,523 --> 00:23:59,873
It's snowing in Minneapolis,
our flight's been delayed.

446
00:23:59,916 --> 00:24:02,005
I don't know when
we'll be leaving.

447
00:24:02,049 --> 00:24:06,401
Well, the roast is in the oven
and is gonna be ready
precisely at seven o'clock.

448
00:24:06,445 --> 00:24:09,926
I'm sorry, Mother,
but I'm sure we're gonna be
a lot later than that.

449
00:24:09,970 --> 00:24:13,452
If you're not here by 8:00,
the entire dinner is
gonna be ruined.

450
00:24:13,495 --> 00:24:15,366
Out of my control, Mother.

451
00:24:15,410 --> 00:24:17,499
You should have come yesterday.

452
00:24:17,543 --> 00:24:20,633
Remember, I said,
"Why don't you bring
the girls in a day early

453
00:24:20,676 --> 00:24:24,071
"so that I can show them
how to prepare a holiday meal?"

454
00:24:24,114 --> 00:24:27,857
Goodness knows they're not gonna
get much advice on menu
planning from their mother.

455
00:24:27,901 --> 00:24:31,252
Well, they know that cereal
isn't only a breakfast food.

456
00:24:31,295 --> 00:24:33,863
In fact, last night's
dinner was cereal.

457
00:24:33,907 --> 00:24:35,299
Madeline!

458
00:24:35,343 --> 00:24:37,040
Uh... Look,
before I go,

459
00:24:37,084 --> 00:24:39,521
do you want to tell me
what you're doing
conspiring with Ellie

460
00:24:39,565 --> 00:24:42,524
on this little photo spread
of fairy tales?

461
00:24:42,568 --> 00:24:44,874
Oh, you know
about the album?

462
00:24:46,049 --> 00:24:47,703
Well, wasn't my idea of course,

463
00:24:47,747 --> 00:24:49,966
but when Ellie called me
and asked me to help her,

464
00:24:50,010 --> 00:24:51,185
how could I refuse?

465
00:24:53,056 --> 00:24:56,364
I was just trying 
to be helpful.

466
00:24:56,407 --> 00:24:58,540
I know you've always
been fond of Matt,

467
00:24:58,584 --> 00:25:00,673
but you just don't understand
how I feel.

468
00:25:00,716 --> 00:25:03,110
In fact, you of all people
should know how I feel.

469
00:25:03,153 --> 00:25:04,503
This is not about me.

470
00:25:04,546 --> 00:25:06,722
Now, your daughter has worked
tremendously hard

471
00:25:06,766 --> 00:25:08,855
putting together that
little book of memories.

472
00:25:08,898 --> 00:25:11,074
And I want you
to accept it.

473
00:25:11,118 --> 00:25:13,163
Graciously.

474
00:25:13,207 --> 00:25:15,992
In case you haven't tuned in,
this little book doesn't have
a happy ending.

475
00:25:16,036 --> 00:25:18,473
Well, maybe it still can.

476
00:25:18,517 --> 00:25:20,562
You really are the queen
of make-believe.

477
00:25:20,606 --> 00:25:22,390
Um... Look, I gotta go.

478
00:25:22,433 --> 00:25:24,348
I will call you as soon
as I know anything.

479
00:25:24,392 --> 00:25:25,959
I'll talk to you later.

480
00:25:26,873 --> 00:25:27,874
[SIGHS]

481
00:25:28,396 --> 00:25:29,528
[SIGHS]

482
00:25:35,055 --> 00:25:38,275
[PEOPLE EXCLAIMING
DISAPPOINTEDLY]

483
00:25:38,319 --> 00:25:42,105
MAN: I told you we should have
left yesterday, but no, you
didn't want to listen to me.

484
00:25:42,149 --> 00:25:44,064
I heard a plane crashed.

485
00:25:44,107 --> 00:25:45,892
Honey, I don't know
where you get this stuff,

486
00:25:45,935 --> 00:25:47,546
the plane did not crash,
it skidded off the runway.

487
00:25:47,589 --> 00:25:49,156
Supposedly started on fire...

488
00:25:49,199 --> 00:25:51,245
It skidded...
I just talked to the guy.Miami, was it?

489
00:25:51,288 --> 00:25:52,768
Miami?

490
00:25:52,812 --> 00:25:54,596
Just left...Do you know the airline?

491
00:25:54,640 --> 00:25:56,119
MSP, I guess,
I don't know.

492
00:25:56,163 --> 00:25:58,382
Excuse me, folks.
Stand back, please.

493
00:26:00,167 --> 00:26:01,777
Excuse me, Officer.

494
00:26:01,821 --> 00:26:03,997
Did the plane crash?
My husband was on
the plane to Miami.

495
00:26:04,040 --> 00:26:05,085
Which one?

496
00:26:05,128 --> 00:26:06,608
I'm not sure,
he just left.

497
00:26:06,652 --> 00:26:08,610
Ma'am, it would be better
to check with his airline.

498
00:26:08,654 --> 00:26:09,959
Did something happen?

499
00:26:10,003 --> 00:26:12,309
I don't know, ma'am,
if you check with Gate 42,

500
00:26:12,353 --> 00:26:14,529
straight down, on the right.
They should have
more information.

501
00:26:14,573 --> 00:26:16,749
MAN: [OVER WALKIE TALKIE] 
Security, what's the status?Paramedics are on their way.

502
00:26:16,792 --> 00:26:19,099
They should be there in
another three to four minutes.

503
00:26:22,145 --> 00:26:24,278
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

504
00:26:25,975 --> 00:26:29,109
I'm afraid we don't
have much information
at this point.

505
00:26:29,152 --> 00:26:31,981
What we do know is that
there was too much snow,

506
00:26:32,025 --> 00:26:34,070
the pilot had to
abort take-off.

507
00:26:34,114 --> 00:26:36,769
And apparently, the plane
slid into a snow-bank.

508
00:26:36,812 --> 00:26:38,292
Is anybody hurt?

509
00:26:38,335 --> 00:26:40,860
We'll give you
more information
as soon as we can.

510
00:26:40,903 --> 00:26:43,253
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

511
00:27:00,836 --> 00:27:01,968
What's going on?

512
00:27:02,011 --> 00:27:03,491
It's Matt's plane.

513
00:27:03,534 --> 00:27:04,666
Is Dad okay?

514
00:27:04,710 --> 00:27:05,928
What happened?

515
00:27:05,972 --> 00:27:08,365
I'm sure everything
is fine. Let's sit down.

516
00:27:08,409 --> 00:27:10,629
Okay? We'll sit down
and wait for them to tell us.

517
00:27:10,672 --> 00:27:12,674
Mom, did they crash?
Did you see anything?

518
00:27:12,718 --> 00:27:14,589
No, I didn't see anything.

519
00:27:14,633 --> 00:27:17,984
There's just so much snow
that the pilot had a hard time
taking off.

520
00:27:18,027 --> 00:27:19,550
Mom, is anyone hurt?

521
00:27:19,594 --> 00:27:22,162
I don't think so, honey,
but they don't know for sure.

522
00:27:22,205 --> 00:27:24,120
I'm sure Daddy's fine.

523
00:27:26,514 --> 00:27:28,255
MAN: [OVER PA SYSTEM] 
Attention, please.

524
00:27:28,298 --> 00:27:33,695
Anyone waiting for passengers 
on-board MSP Flight 1102 
to Miami,

525
00:27:33,739 --> 00:27:37,568
the plane is now safely 
returning to Gate 75.

526
00:27:40,789 --> 00:27:42,051
Can I get you another one?

527
00:27:42,095 --> 00:27:44,706
Oh, no, no,
it's okay, thanks.

528
00:27:44,750 --> 00:27:46,926
You look like you must
have someone on that plane.

529
00:27:46,969 --> 00:27:48,841
Yeah, my 10-year-old son.

530
00:27:48,884 --> 00:27:50,625
Oh, I'm sorry.

531
00:27:50,669 --> 00:27:52,061
I let him fly alone.

532
00:27:52,105 --> 00:27:54,107
It was the first time
I let him fly alone.

533
00:27:54,150 --> 00:27:55,369
Dad!Oh, Jason.

534
00:27:55,412 --> 00:27:56,936
You okay?

535
00:27:56,979 --> 00:27:58,720
The plane felt like
it was gonna crash
or something.

536
00:27:58,764 --> 00:28:01,331
Then everybody
started freaking out.

537
00:28:01,375 --> 00:28:03,769
