559
00:29:00,956 --> 00:29:02,305
Oh, okay.

560
00:29:02,349 --> 00:29:04,699
Prosecutor?
Public defender?

561
00:29:04,743 --> 00:29:06,309
Mergers and acquisitions.

562
00:29:06,701 --> 00:29:08,007
Ooh.

563
00:29:11,575 --> 00:29:14,143
Well, I better go.

564
00:29:14,187 --> 00:29:15,797
It was nice to
see you again.

565
00:29:15,841 --> 00:29:18,104
Yeah, great to see you.
Great to see you.

566
00:29:18,147 --> 00:29:19,453
Nice to meet you, Jason.

567
00:29:19,496 --> 00:29:21,542
Thanks, bye.

568
00:29:21,585 --> 00:29:23,152
We went
to grade school together.

569
00:29:26,503 --> 00:29:28,027
ELLIE: Dad!

570
00:29:28,070 --> 00:29:29,028
Ellie!

571
00:29:29,593 --> 00:29:30,638
Dad!

572
00:29:31,247 --> 00:29:32,553
Hi, Kirby.

573
00:29:34,163 --> 00:29:36,165
Are you all right?Yeah, not a scratch.

574
00:29:36,209 --> 00:29:39,778
Wasn't half as wild as being
on the field after the world
series, remember that?

575
00:29:39,821 --> 00:29:42,171
That was scary.Sure was.

576
00:29:42,215 --> 00:29:43,869
Dad, what are we
gonna do now?

577
00:29:43,912 --> 00:29:45,305
Well, uh...

578
00:29:46,219 --> 00:29:48,351
We can't fly.

579
00:29:48,395 --> 00:29:50,658
And we can't drive.

580
00:29:50,701 --> 00:29:54,183
So, unless they rent out
sleighs, looks like we're stuck

581
00:29:54,227 --> 00:29:55,663
together.

582
00:30:04,280 --> 00:30:05,934
I have to tell you something.

583
00:30:07,544 --> 00:30:09,242
Hey, you know what?

584
00:30:09,285 --> 00:30:10,896
I'm gonna go see if I can
get some information
on our flights.

585
00:30:10,939 --> 00:30:12,027
Great.

586
00:30:12,071 --> 00:30:13,246
Who wants to
come with me?

587
00:30:13,289 --> 00:30:14,595
BOTH: I do!

588
00:30:14,638 --> 00:30:16,466
[CHUCKLING] Let's go.
We'll catch up with you.

589
00:30:16,510 --> 00:30:17,816
Bye, Mom.Bye, girls.

