Some deal with
the All Sports Channel.

595
00:30:26,868 --> 00:30:29,915
My life is going down the toilet
and he's gonna be on TV.

596
00:30:29,958 --> 00:30:32,613
Guess Matt finally
realized you weren't
gonna take him back.

597
00:30:32,656 --> 00:30:35,268
He's gonna be
shuttling the girls around
every weekend.

598
00:30:35,311 --> 00:30:38,532
Don't you guys think
it's time to tell them that
you're getting divorced?

599
00:30:38,575 --> 00:30:40,534
We decided to wait
until after the holidays.

600
00:30:40,577 --> 00:30:42,014
But they suspect.

601
00:30:51,414 --> 00:30:53,242
WOMAN: How much longer
will it take?

602
00:30:53,286 --> 00:30:55,592
I'm sorry, ma'am.
I don't know.

603
00:30:59,727 --> 00:31:01,511
Dad.

604
00:31:01,555 --> 00:31:04,688
It starts with an "S".
Six letters across.

605
00:31:04,732 --> 00:31:06,908
It's the name
of a planet.

606
00:31:06,952 --> 00:31:08,170
You know that.

607
00:31:09,563 --> 00:31:11,217
Sa...

608
00:31:11,260 --> 00:31:12,871
Saturn?Yeah.

609
00:31:13,915 --> 00:31:17,092
S-A-T-U-R-N.
I got it.

610
00:31:18,267 --> 00:31:19,616
Can you open this
for me, Daddy?

611
00:31:19,660 --> 00:31:20,704
Sure.

612
00:31:22,358 --> 00:31:23,490
Thanks.

613
00:31:23,533 --> 00:31:25,927
Dad, why can't you
come to Grandma's?

614
00:31:25,971 --> 00:31:27,973
You already missed your plane.

615
00:31:28,016 --> 00:31:32,629
A light that shoots
across the sky.
Eleven letters down...

616
00:31:32,673 --> 00:31:34,414
Kirby,

617
00:31:34,457 --> 00:31:36,459
remember what
we talked about?

618
00:31:36,503 --> 00:31:38,897
Yeah. You and Mom
needed time.

619
00:31:38,940 --> 00:31:40,724
But haven't you
had enough time?

620
00:31:40,768 --> 00:31:42,813
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING]

621
00:31:42,857 --> 00:31:46,513
I promised my Dad
I'd spend Christmas with him.

622
00:31:46,556 --> 00:31:49,385
You know how important
it is to keep your promises.

623
00:31:59,874 --> 00:32:01,963
Do you think
I should cut my hair like this?

624
00:32:02,007 --> 00:32:04,618
No, I like your hair.

625
00:32:04,661 --> 00:32:05,924
Oh, great, it's broken.

626
00:32:05,967 --> 00:32:07,969
Come on, let's go get
some coffee upstairs.

627
00:32:08,013 --> 00:32:09,144
What about the color?

628
00:32:09,188 --> 00:32:10,754
Maddie, you look great.

629
00:32:10,798 --> 00:32:12,104
I don't feel great.

630
00:32:12,147 --> 00:32:13,844
Don't be so hard on yourself.

631
00:32:13,888 --> 00:32:16,021
I'm just so angry with him.

632
00:32:16,064 --> 00:32:17,674
You've made that
perfectly clear.

633
00:32:17,718 --> 00:32:18,849
You know,

634
00:32:18,893 --> 00:32:20,373
ever since we split up,

635
00:32:20,416 --> 00:32:23,245
you have done nothing
but minimize what
Matt did to me.

636
00:32:23,289 --> 00:32:26,596
Maddie, what he did
was horrible and stupid.

637
00:32:26,640 --> 00:32:29,904
And when I found out about it,
part of me hated him for it.

638
00:32:29,948 --> 00:32:34,213
But I know you guys,
I know how much
you love each other.

639
00:32:34,256 --> 00:32:37,825
After 15 years, don't you
at least want to hear
what he has to say?

640
00:32:37,868 --> 00:32:39,609
No, I don't.

641
00:32:39,653 --> 00:32:41,002
Look, Katherine,

642
00:32:41,046 --> 00:32:43,004
he destroyed everything
we had together.

643
00:32:43,048 --> 00:32:46,268
He betrayed my trust
and sorry is not enough.

644
00:32:46,312 --> 00:32:48,488
And stop being
so nice to him.

645
00:32:48,531 --> 00:32:51,882
Maddie, he'll always be
Ellie and Kirby's father.

646
00:32:51,926 --> 00:32:53,710
Yeah, well, he won't
always be my husband.

647
00:32:53,754 --> 00:32:55,451
All right.

648
00:32:55,495 --> 00:32:57,888
WOMAN: [ON TV] Hi, everybody. 
