Thanks.

1256
01:05:13,561 --> 01:05:15,999
This purse contains
the story of my life.

1257
01:05:16,042 --> 01:05:18,001
Hm! Efficient packer.

1258
01:05:18,044 --> 01:05:19,828
I think I'd need a trunk.

1259
01:05:20,438 --> 01:05:21,656
Is that Hawaii?

1260
01:05:21,700 --> 01:05:23,615
Yes.

1261
01:05:23,658 --> 01:05:26,009
My husband and I
dreamed to go on there.

1262
01:05:26,052 --> 01:05:27,924
We were saving.

1263
01:05:27,967 --> 01:05:30,796
And look at you in that
bikini, you look great.

1264
01:05:30,839 --> 01:05:32,798
Well, 1982 BC.

1265
01:05:32,841 --> 01:05:34,191
Before children.

1266
01:05:35,453 --> 01:05:36,497
May I?

1267
01:05:36,541 --> 01:05:37,672
Please.

1268
01:05:40,153 --> 01:05:42,416
I wish I had more pictures
of my family.

1269
01:05:42,460 --> 01:05:44,897
Well, proves
you had one, right?

1270
01:05:46,029 --> 01:05:47,030
I'm Maddie.

1271
01:05:47,073 --> 01:05:48,118
Gwen.

1272
01:05:48,596 --> 01:05:49,641
Hi.

1273
01:05:51,208 --> 01:05:53,427
My husband and our son,

1274
01:05:53,471 --> 01:05:55,386
Deshawn, six now.

1275
01:05:56,039 --> 01:05:57,301
Handsome family.

1276
01:05:58,041 --> 01:05:59,607
Thank you.

1277
01:05:59,651 --> 01:06:02,175
Do you and your husband
get any time
to yourselves now?

1278
01:06:02,219 --> 01:06:04,003
He died three years ago.

1279
01:06:04,047 --> 01:06:06,005
Shot breaking up a fight.

1280
01:06:06,049 --> 01:06:07,180
He was a cop.

1281
01:06:07,224 --> 01:06:09,574
Oh, I'm so sorry.

1282
01:06:09,617 --> 01:06:12,011
We're doing okay,
Deshawn and I.

1283
01:06:12,055 --> 01:06:15,014
I take classes at the university
during the day.

1284
01:06:15,058 --> 01:06:17,234
And I work out here at night.

1285
01:06:17,277 --> 01:06:19,192
My mother looks
after my son.

1286
01:06:20,019 --> 01:06:21,455
That must be hard.

1287
01:06:22,413 --> 01:06:24,154
Yeah.

1288
01:06:24,197 --> 01:06:28,593
But I just thank the good Lord
that our last words were kind.

1289
01:06:28,636 --> 01:06:32,075
We'd been fighting over
something the night before.

1290
01:06:32,118 --> 01:06:36,035
But my husband, Philip,
had a house rule.

1291
01:06:36,079 --> 01:06:39,343
No leaving without some loving.

1292
01:06:39,386 --> 01:06:40,997
So the next morning,

1293
01:06:41,040 --> 01:06:44,261
he snuck up behind me
in the kitchen
and kissed me.

1294
01:06:45,175 --> 01:06:46,828
'Cause you just never know.

1295
01:06:49,266 --> 01:06:50,832
WOMAN: [OVER PA SYSTEM] 
Madeline Parker,

1296
01:06:50,876 --> 01:06:53,661
please meet your party 
at the Concourse Restaurant, 
level two.

1297
01:06:53,705 --> 01:06:55,098
It's my sister, finally.

1298
01:06:55,141 --> 01:06:56,708
Madeline Parker,

1299
01:06:56,751 --> 01:06:59,276
please meet your party 
at the Concourse Restaurant, 
level two.

1300
01:06:59,319 --> 01:07:00,581
Have a great holiday, Gwen.

1301
01:07:01,800 --> 01:07:03,410
You too.

1302
01:07:03,454 --> 01:07:05,412
And don't forget to
take lots of pictures.

1303
01:07:16,771 --> 01:07:18,773
Girls!Jason.

1304
01:07:18,817 --> 01:07:20,993
KATHERINE: What are you
doing up there?

1305
01:07:21,037 --> 01:07:23,213
You didn't even
notice we were gone.

1306
01:07:23,256 --> 01:07:24,910
How did you get up there?

1307
01:07:24,953 --> 01:07:26,607
The escalator.

1308
01:07:26,651 --> 01:07:29,175
Well, take the escalator
back down, please.

1309
01:07:29,741 --> 01:07:30,829
Fine.

1310
01:07:33,440 --> 01:07:35,094
Did we notice
they were gone?

1311
01:07:35,138 --> 01:07:36,356
Who?

1312
01:07:36,400 --> 01:07:38,271
The kids.

1313
01:07:38,315 --> 01:07:41,057
Oh, yeah, of course
we noticed, I mean...

1314
01:07:41,100 --> 01:07:43,624
That's why we came
running out here.

1315
01:07:45,104 --> 01:07:46,105
Yeah.

1316
01:07:47,454 --> 01:07:49,369
They look like
they're having fun.

1317
01:07:49,413 --> 01:07:50,457
Oh, yeah.

1318
01:07:51,415 --> 01:07:52,894
So was I.

1319
01:08:01,207 --> 01:08:02,513
Maddie Parker?

1320
01:08:02,556 --> 01:08:04,210
Yes.This way, please.

1321
01:08:04,254 --> 01:08:06,125
[ROMANTIC PIANO MUSIC PLAYING]

1322
01:08:09,824 --> 01:08:11,348
I don't understand.

1323
01:08:11,391 --> 01:08:13,001
This is your table.

1324
01:08:14,046 --> 01:08:16,396
Oh... Uh...

1325
01:08:29,757 --> 01:08:32,151
Remember the last time
we were stuck in this airport?

1326
01:08:32,195 --> 01:08:34,762
Grad school, spring break,
our first trip together.

1327
01:08:34,806 --> 01:08:37,722
Our plane was delayed
almost four hours,

1328
01:08:37,765 --> 01:08:39,027
but it didn't matter,

1329
01:08:39,071 --> 01:08:42,379
because I was exactly
where I wanted to be.

1330
01:08:43,858 --> 01:08:44,903
What are you doing?

1331
01:08:45,643 --> 01:08:46,948
Wooing you.

1332
01:08:48,124 --> 01:08:50,387
Wooing me?

1333
01:08:50,430 --> 01:08:53,390
I'm a little out of practice,
but I used to be
pretty good at it.

1334
01:08:59,396 --> 01:09:01,267
Give me a chance, Maddie.

1335
01:09:03,748 --> 01:09:06,229
I better find Katherine
and the girls.

1336
01:09:06,272 --> 01:09:09,449
I'm sure Aunt Katherine's
got everything under control.

1337
01:09:19,677 --> 01:09:20,939
Come on.

1338
01:09:25,248 --> 01:09:26,249
Just for a minute.

1339
01:09:26,292 --> 01:09:27,467
Okay.

1340
01:09:32,777 --> 01:09:36,215
One for you. One for you.
One for me. One for you.

1341
01:09:36,259 --> 01:09:38,174
Give me something
good this time.

1342
01:09:38,217 --> 01:09:40,132
You keep winning.

1343
01:09:40,176 --> 01:09:41,960
KIRBY: Tell me about it!

1344
01:10:06,376 --> 01:10:08,334
Hey, where's your ring?

1345
01:10:08,378 --> 01:10:11,642
Oh, I took it off this morning.

1346
01:10:11,685 --> 01:10:14,471
I'm surprised to see
you're still wearing yours.

1347
01:10:14,514 --> 01:10:16,212
Still didn't want
to take it off.

1348
01:10:26,831 --> 01:10:28,398
What did I do wrong?

1349
01:10:29,747 --> 01:10:31,139
You?

1350
01:10:31,183 --> 01:10:33,272
Nothing. I'm the one
who messed things up.

1351
01:10:33,316 --> 01:10:36,797
[SIGHS] I'm sure
there's enough blame
to go around.

1352
01:10:41,411 --> 01:10:43,500
Do you remember
the good times

1353
01:10:43,543 --> 01:10:45,371
or has it turned into
one big regret?

1354
01:10:48,853 --> 01:10:51,508
You are the only man
I ever wanted to marry.

1355
01:10:53,074 --> 01:10:56,252
I don't regret
following my heart.

1356
01:10:58,254 --> 01:11:02,867
I'm sorry that somewhere
along the way, that young couple
got lost, Maddie.

1357
01:11:02,910 --> 01:11:06,305
Yeah, somewhere
between jobs and kids

1358
01:11:06,349 --> 01:11:09,482
and a million errands
that had to be run.

1359
01:11:09,526 --> 01:11:13,530
On my to-do list,
not much time for us.

1360
01:11:15,880 --> 01:11:17,882
Remember...

1361
01:11:17,925 --> 01:11:20,972
when we first
moved into the house,
I installed that dimmer

1362
01:11:21,015 --> 01:11:24,802
so that we would
always feel like
we were dining by candlelight?

1363
01:11:27,631 --> 01:11:29,763
When was the last time
I turned that thing on?

1364
01:11:29,807 --> 01:11:31,461
I don't know.

1365
01:11:31,504 --> 01:11:34,290
I wouldn't mind
a little ambiance with
my peanut butter and pizza.

1366
01:11:36,814 --> 01:11:39,469
Who were we before
we were Mom and Dad?

1367
01:11:44,691 --> 01:11:47,346
We were people
who liked to dance.

1368
01:11:56,137 --> 01:11:57,835
[PLAYING JAZZ MUSIC]

1369
01:12:37,004 --> 01:12:38,615
I need some air.

1370
01:12:42,053 --> 01:12:44,142
[SNORING LOUDLY]

1371
01:13:02,900 --> 01:13:04,510
WOMAN: [OVER PA SYSTEM] 
Attention, passengers.

1372
01:13:04,554 --> 01:13:06,338
The plows have cleared 
the runways

1373
01:13:06,382 --> 01:13:08,862
and we hope 
to resume service shortly.

1374
01:13:08,906 --> 01:13:11,865
Please check your airlines 
for revised schedules.

1375
01:13:12,779 --> 01:13:14,128
Maddie, wait.

1376
01:13:14,999 --> 01:13:16,479
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

1377
01:13:16,522 --> 01:13:17,784
Maddie?

1378
01:13:22,398 --> 01:13:24,748
Snow is so beautiful,
isn't it?

1379
01:13:24,791 --> 01:13:26,619
Yeah,
sure is.

1380
01:13:26,663 --> 01:13:28,839
What a mess it's made
of our day.

1381
01:13:30,188 --> 01:13:31,711
It's almost 10:30.

1382
01:13:31,755 --> 01:13:34,453
You should have been
in Florida hours ago.

1383
01:13:34,497 --> 01:13:36,368
We should be
in Chicago.

1384
01:13:36,412 --> 01:13:38,152
They said,
"A chance of snow."

1385
01:13:38,718 --> 01:13:40,111
"A chance"?

1386
01:13:41,939 --> 01:13:44,507
I don't know
about you,

1387
01:13:44,550 --> 01:13:47,118
but I was kind of nervous
back there. I mean,

1388
01:13:47,161 --> 01:13:50,469
it felt like we were
a couple of kids, almost

1389
01:13:51,470 --> 01:13:52,515
like our first date.

1390
01:13:55,256 --> 01:13:57,520
Big Ten Hockey
Championship.

1391
01:13:58,042 --> 01:13:59,478
Yeah.

1392
01:13:59,522 --> 01:14:01,306
You asked me to
meet you outside
the locker room

1393
01:14:01,349 --> 01:14:02,916
afterwards, remember?

1394
01:14:03,700 --> 01:14:05,136
Your team had just won,

1395
01:14:05,179 --> 01:14:08,095
people were going crazy
dancing in the streets.

1396
01:14:08,139 --> 01:14:10,097
There were so many girls
running after you.

1397
01:14:11,055 --> 01:14:12,448
I only had eyes

1398
01:14:13,840 --> 01:14:15,407
for one of them.

1399
01:14:31,641 --> 01:14:33,512
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

1400
01:14:44,305 --> 01:14:46,786
I'm sorry, I'm usually
the life of the party.

1401
01:14:56,404 --> 01:14:58,189
You said you painted houses.

1402
01:14:58,232 --> 01:14:59,495
I do.

1403
01:14:59,538 --> 01:15:01,540
You should see
my window trims.

1404
01:15:02,628 --> 01:15:05,413
But this is so professional.

1405
01:15:05,457 --> 01:15:07,633
You could sell work like this.

1406
01:15:07,677 --> 01:15:09,548
Yeah, I do on occasion.

1407
01:15:09,592 --> 01:15:13,334
But for now,
with a boy who needs books
and computer games

1408
01:15:13,378 --> 01:15:16,076
and tuition, I've gotta
concentrate on

1409
01:15:16,120 --> 01:15:18,949
Johnson Interior
and Exterior House Painting.

1410
01:15:18,992 --> 01:15:21,734
"Quality work at
reasonable prices."

1411
01:15:21,778 --> 01:15:23,693
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

1412
01:15:25,259 --> 01:15:26,652
Would you sign it for me?

1413
01:15:27,131 --> 01:15:28,567
Be happy to.

1414
01:15:36,009 --> 01:15:38,272
Thanks for making me
look so good.

1415
01:15:39,360 --> 01:15:42,668
Oh, yeah, well,
it was awfully easy.

1416
01:15:47,412 --> 01:15:50,850
The girls are
practically teenagers,
which can only help.

1417
01:15:50,894 --> 01:15:52,548
I mean, they're not
gonna need constant attention,

1418
01:15:52,591 --> 01:15:54,854
we can find time
for us again.

1419
01:15:54,898 --> 01:15:57,030
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1420
01:15:57,074 --> 01:15:58,945
What do you say,

1421
01:15:58,989 --> 01:16:00,730
we take off somewhere
in a couple of weeks,

1422
01:16:00,773 --> 01:16:02,819
just you and me, hm?

1423
01:16:05,561 --> 01:16:06,736
How about Hawaii?

1424
01:16:06,779 --> 01:16:08,868
We haven't been back
since our honeymoon.

1425
01:16:10,348 --> 01:16:11,436
How about it?

1426
01:16:11,479 --> 01:16:13,830
You and me
on a beach somewhere.

1427
01:16:16,006 --> 01:16:20,271
I bet you still got
a string bikini tucked away
in a drawer.

1428
01:16:20,314 --> 01:16:22,186
I don't think that's
gonna work for me.

1429
01:16:22,229 --> 01:16:24,275
How come?

1430
01:16:24,318 --> 01:16:27,147
For one thing,
the suit won't fit.

1431
01:16:27,191 --> 01:16:28,801
Come on, what are you
talking about?

1432
01:16:28,845 --> 01:16:31,064
You haven't gained
five pounds in 15 years.

1433
01:16:33,414 --> 01:16:35,591
Except when I was pregnant.

1434
01:16:43,424 --> 01:16:44,600
You're not...

1435
01:16:46,689 --> 01:16:47,733
I am.

1436
01:16:48,560 --> 01:16:49,822
Three months.

1437
01:16:59,789 --> 01:17:01,268
MERILEE: [OVER PHONE] 
Maddie, what's the matter?

1438
01:17:01,704 --> 01:17:02,792
Nothing.

1439
01:17:03,967 --> 01:17:05,664
It's Matt, isn't it?

1440
01:17:06,926 --> 01:17:08,058
Yes.

1441
01:17:09,450 --> 01:17:10,930
I'm gonna tell you
a little secret

1442
01:17:10,974 --> 01:17:14,499
that you're not gonna find
in any of my damn guide books.

1443
01:17:14,542 --> 01:17:18,895
[LAUGHING] A Happy Homemaker.
Oh, what a joke!

1444
01:17:18,938 --> 01:17:21,724
Most nights I'm sitting here
looking at the television

1445
01:17:21,767 --> 01:17:23,682
and grabbing a book

1446
01:17:23,726 --> 01:17:26,859
and climbing into
my empty four-poster.

1447
01:17:27,512 --> 01:17:29,079
Maddie,

1448
01:17:29,122 --> 01:17:32,082
it's been almost 25 years 
since your father left.

1449
01:17:32,125 --> 01:17:37,478
I was too proud
and too stubborn to go
and try and stop him.

1450
01:17:37,522 --> 01:17:39,176
You still miss Dad?

1451
01:17:39,219 --> 01:17:41,700
That's right.

1452
01:17:41,744 --> 01:17:44,660
My first book was selling 
better that the Bible

1453
01:17:44,703 --> 01:17:46,183
and that was the proof, right?

1454
01:17:46,226 --> 01:17:49,360
That I was the perfect mother,
the perfect wife,

1455
01:17:49,403 --> 01:17:51,362
and the perfect fool.

1456
01:17:53,233 --> 01:17:55,540
Then, a little while later,

1457
01:17:55,583 --> 01:17:58,674
he fell in love with someone.

1458
01:17:58,717 --> 01:18:01,415
Married 23 years this summer,
Dad and Audrey.

1459
01:18:01,459 --> 01:18:03,983
Yup. You might wanna add
"happily married."

1460
01:18:04,027 --> 01:18:05,637
Mom,

1461
01:18:05,681 --> 01:18:09,989
I always thought it would be
the same for me and Matt.

1462
01:18:10,033 --> 01:18:14,428
I didn't really imagine that
marriage would be this hard.

1463
01:18:14,472 --> 01:18:17,910
Well, you see, that's where
so many of us get screwed up.

1464
01:18:17,954 --> 01:18:20,783
We exchange rings,
we make a few promises,

1465
01:18:20,826 --> 01:18:24,090
and then we expect to
spend the next 50 years
with our heads in the clouds.

1466
01:18:24,134 --> 01:18:25,657
Well, that's bull!

1467
01:18:25,701 --> 01:18:27,877
We work hard at our careers.

1468
01:18:27,920 --> 01:18:30,140
We work hard at
keeping our figures

1469
01:18:30,183 --> 01:18:33,404
and we read all the books we can
about raising our children.

1470
01:18:33,447 --> 01:18:35,362
But work at marriage,
are you kidding?

1471
01:18:35,406 --> 01:18:37,625
Nobody works at romance.

1472
01:18:37,669 --> 01:18:42,326
Trust me, Maddie, 
true romance is holding 
the wrinkled, old hand

1473
01:18:42,369 --> 01:18:45,416
of the person 
that you've been clinging to 
for 50 years.

1474
01:18:45,459 --> 01:18:48,724
Not spritz of perfume
and candlelight

1475
01:18:48,767 --> 01:18:50,682
and under the covers
with number 14.

1476
01:18:51,161 --> 01:18:52,684
Fourteen?

1477
01:18:52,728 --> 01:18:55,818
It's just a figure of speech,
Maddie, not a confession.

1478
01:18:58,821 --> 01:19:02,172
Well, I haven't exactly been
cloistered all these years,

1479
01:19:02,215 --> 01:19:04,435
but, you know,

1480
01:19:04,478 --> 01:19:07,220
I've never met a man that
I wanted to be married to

1481
01:19:07,264 --> 01:19:08,744
the way I did your father.

1482
01:19:10,223 --> 01:19:12,573
Why are you telling me all this?

1483
01:19:12,617 --> 01:19:15,968
Maddie, when does 
Matt's plane leave?

1484
01:19:16,534 --> 01:19:17,665
Uh...

1485
01:19:18,536 --> 01:19:20,494
About ten minutes.

1486
01:19:20,538 --> 01:19:22,018
That's why.

1487
01:19:22,061 --> 01:19:26,413
Sweetheart, if Matt walks
through that gate, he's gone.

1488
01:19:26,457 --> 01:19:28,851
And you'll have no one 
to blame but yourself.

1489
01:19:28,894 --> 01:19:32,811
But if you 
don't love him, well...

1490
01:19:32,855 --> 01:19:38,817
Then just go to your gate
and flip through a magazine
and, you know, relax.

1491
01:19:38,861 --> 01:19:41,472
I'm sorry I didn't read
your last three books, Mom,

1492
01:19:41,515 --> 01:19:43,517
because you know what?

1493
01:19:43,561 --> 01:19:45,128
You have some
pretty good advice.

1494
01:19:46,825 --> 01:19:48,087
Um...

1495
01:19:48,131 --> 01:19:49,915
I'm gonna run now.

1496
01:19:49,959 --> 01:19:52,918
And I'll call you.

1497
01:19:53,484 --> 01:19:54,528
Bye bye.

1498
01:19:57,618 --> 01:19:59,446
WOMAN: [OVER PA SYSTEM] 
Attention passengers,

1499
01:19:59,490 --> 01:20:02,319
this is the final 
boarding call...

1500
01:20:06,714 --> 01:20:07,715
Excuse me.

1501
01:20:26,473 --> 01:20:28,084
I need to talk to
someone on the plane.

1502
01:20:28,127 --> 01:20:29,955
Oh, I'm sorry, the plane
just pulled out.

1503
01:20:29,999 --> 01:20:31,130
Are you sure?

1504
01:20:31,174 --> 01:20:33,654
Yes, about
five minutes ago.

1505
01:20:36,135 --> 01:20:37,484
Thank you.

1506
01:20:40,923 --> 01:20:43,969
REBECCA: [ON TV] Good news 
out there, the storm that 
we've been watching

1507
01:20:44,013 --> 01:20:47,016
throughout the last 12 hours 
is finally starting 
to taper off.

1508
01:20:47,059 --> 01:20:49,757
That's great news, 
especially for a lot 
of people traveling.

1509
01:20:49,801 --> 01:20:53,761
In fact we have received word 
at the Minneapolis 
St. Paul International Airport

1510
01:20:53,805 --> 01:20:55,633
that runways are now open

1511
01:20:55,676 --> 01:20:57,896
so they're going to try 
to get some 
of the flights going.

1512
01:20:57,940 --> 01:21:00,507
A lot of people have been 
stranded there and I know 
this is good news,

1513
01:21:00,551 --> 01:21:03,032
that you can get to 
your loved ones for Christmas.

1514
01:21:03,075 --> 01:21:05,599
And for the kids out there 
still watching TV,

1515
01:21:05,643 --> 01:21:09,690
the best part. It looks like 
Santa Claus will be able to 
make it to the Twin Cities.

1516
01:21:09,734 --> 01:21:11,431
So your wish 
will come true.

1517
01:21:12,606 --> 01:21:14,304
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

1518
01:21:25,315 --> 01:21:26,664
My bag.

1519
01:21:33,889 --> 01:21:35,064
Excuse me.

1520
01:21:52,211 --> 01:21:53,343
Oh, God!

1521
01:21:53,386 --> 01:21:54,779
Hey!

1522
01:21:54,822 --> 01:21:57,869
I'm sorry,
I was just checking.
I lost my purse.

1523
01:21:57,913 --> 01:21:58,914
Excuse me.

1524
01:22:10,664 --> 01:22:13,319
Gwen! Gwen!

1525
01:22:13,363 --> 01:22:16,409
I left my bag in
the phone booth,
my photo album was in it.

1526
01:22:16,453 --> 01:22:19,108
Okay, just try to
stay calm, what else
was in your bag?

1527
01:22:19,151 --> 01:22:21,110
Well, I've got the plane tickets
in my pocket,

1528
01:22:21,153 --> 01:22:23,329
but everything else,
my wallet, my keys, my ring.

1529
01:22:23,373 --> 01:22:24,461
Your ring?

1530
01:22:24,504 --> 01:22:25,679
Oh, that doesn't matter.

1531
01:22:25,723 --> 01:22:27,681
The most important thing
is that photo album.

1532
01:22:27,725 --> 01:22:29,205
My daughter worked
so hard on it.

1533
01:22:29,248 --> 01:22:31,947
Jim, this is Gwen.
Do you copy?

1534
01:22:31,990 --> 01:22:34,166
JIM: I copy.

1535
01:22:34,210 --> 01:22:37,996
GWEN: We're looking for 
a photo album and a purse 
last seen on the red concourse.

1536
01:22:38,040 --> 01:22:39,867
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

1537
01:23:03,326 --> 01:23:04,544
GWEN: Maddie.

1538
01:23:05,415 --> 01:23:06,938
I'm sorry.

1539
01:23:06,982 --> 01:23:08,722
This is all
we could find.

1540
01:23:18,732 --> 01:23:20,996
Looks good, and here you go.

1541
01:23:26,523 --> 01:23:31,615
WOMAN: [OVER PA SYSTEM] 
MSP Flight 523 will be 
boarding in five minutes.

1542
01:23:31,658 --> 01:23:36,489
That's MSP Flight 523, 
will be boarding 
in five minutes.

1543
01:23:36,533 --> 01:23:37,621
Did they find it?

1544
01:23:37,664 --> 01:23:39,057
Mm-mm. No.

1545
01:23:44,802 --> 01:23:48,110
I'm sorry I never thanked you
for the present.

1546
01:23:48,153 --> 01:23:50,503
Took a lot of work to
organize all those photos

1547
01:23:50,547 --> 01:23:53,115
and you did
a beautiful job.

1548
01:23:53,158 --> 01:23:57,771
I was meant to do it myself,
but I never took the time.

1549
01:23:57,815 --> 01:24:01,732
You made me think about
all the wonderful times
that this family's had.

1550
01:24:05,040 --> 01:24:07,172
Do you think
they'll ever find it?

1551
01:24:10,001 --> 01:24:12,003
I wish they would,
Ellie, but I...

1552
01:24:13,091 --> 01:24:14,397
I'm afraid
the album's gone.

1553
01:24:19,967 --> 01:24:24,189
We won't be taking
any more family photos,
will we, Mom?

1554
01:24:24,233 --> 01:24:27,105
Honey, no matter what happens
between your father and me,

1555
01:24:27,149 --> 01:24:29,064
we'll always be a family.

1556
01:24:31,501 --> 01:24:34,069
It won't be the same.

1557
01:24:34,112 --> 01:24:37,159
Not if we're never
in the same pictures.

1558
01:24:37,202 --> 01:24:39,248
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING]

1559
01:24:50,433 --> 01:24:52,304
WOMAN: [OVER PA SYSTEM] 
Ladies and gentlemen,

1560
01:24:52,348 --> 01:24:56,003
MSP Flight 523 
is now boarding.

1561
01:24:56,047 --> 01:24:58,484
It's about time.

1562
01:24:58,528 --> 01:25:02,967
Who would have thought
I'd run into this goofy kid
I knew in grade school.

1563
01:25:03,010 --> 01:25:06,144
Now he's a single dad
who paints sheet rock
for a living.

1564
01:25:06,188 --> 01:25:09,974
And all of a sudden,
I'm writing
"lasagna at Craig's"

1565
01:25:10,017 --> 01:25:12,542
in my Filofax
with a happy face next to it.

1566
01:25:12,585 --> 01:25:14,370
You drew a happy face?

1567
01:25:14,413 --> 01:25:16,850
Yeah. Can you believe it?

1568
01:25:16,894 --> 01:25:18,896
This may be a good thing
for you, you know.

1569
01:25:18,939 --> 01:25:23,248
Nice guy, more concerned
about being a good father
than building his portfolio.

1570
01:25:23,292 --> 01:25:24,380
You think?

1571
01:25:24,423 --> 01:25:25,511
Absolutely.

1572
01:25:27,252 --> 01:25:29,733
Well, I'm just sorry
about you and Matt.

1573
01:25:29,776 --> 01:25:32,039
Really thought things
would turn out differently.

1574
01:25:32,083 --> 01:25:34,781
[SIGHS] It's over.

1575
01:25:34,825 --> 01:25:38,133
I can't believe you told him
about the baby
and he still got on that plane.

1576
01:25:39,221 --> 01:25:41,397
I didn't really
give him a chance.

1577
01:25:44,487 --> 01:25:46,010
Don't you worry, Maddie.

1578
01:25:46,053 --> 01:25:48,230
I'm gonna be there
every step of the way.

1579
01:25:48,273 --> 01:25:50,928
I'll go to those
breathing classes with you,

1580
01:25:50,971 --> 01:25:53,191
hold your hand
in the delivery room.

1581
01:25:53,235 --> 01:25:54,758
I promise.

1582
01:25:54,801 --> 01:25:57,326
I'll even learn how to change
a diaper or two.

1583
01:25:57,369 --> 01:25:59,328
We'll get through this
together, okay?

1584
01:26:02,026 --> 01:26:05,290
WOMAN: [OVER PA SYSTEM] 
Will Madeline Parker please 
come to the lost and found?

1585
01:26:05,334 --> 01:26:07,031
Madeline Parker, please 
come to the lost and found?

1586
01:26:07,074 --> 01:26:08,163
Board without me.

1587
01:26:08,206 --> 01:26:09,468
You're gonna miss the plane.

1588
01:26:09,512 --> 01:26:11,078
Katherine, I need
those pictures.

1589
01:26:11,122 --> 01:26:13,124
Mom, Mom,
I wanna go with you.

1590
01:26:13,168 --> 01:26:15,126
Go with Aunt Kat,
I'll be right back.

1591
01:26:15,170 --> 01:26:17,433
Come on, come on.
It's okay.

1592
01:26:25,180 --> 01:26:27,225
You paged for Parker-Hill...

1593
01:26:34,754 --> 01:26:35,886
Maddie.Gwen!

1594
01:26:35,929 --> 01:26:36,974
You were in luck.

1595
01:26:37,757 --> 01:26:39,759
You found it.

1596
01:26:39,803 --> 01:26:41,239
We found it in
a recycle bin.

1597
01:26:41,283 --> 01:26:42,719
Thank you.

1598
01:26:42,762 --> 01:26:44,938
I hope you're not
as sentimental
about your purse.

1599
01:26:44,982 --> 01:26:46,070
That's gone.

1600
01:26:46,766 --> 01:26:47,811
You know what I wish?

1601
01:26:47,854 --> 01:26:50,596
I wish we'd taken
more photographs.

1602
01:26:50,640 --> 01:26:51,728
MATT: Yeah.

1603
01:26:51,771 --> 01:26:53,208
Me too.

1604
01:27:01,781 --> 01:27:03,087
What are you doing here?

1605
01:27:03,130 --> 01:27:05,089
You're supposed
to be on a plane.

1606
01:27:05,132 --> 01:27:06,612
I realized that...

1607
01:27:08,832 --> 01:27:10,573
I don't wanna
go anywhere.

1608
01:27:10,616 --> 01:27:12,052
For Christmas?

1609
01:27:12,096 --> 01:27:13,315
For good.

1610
01:27:15,578 --> 01:27:18,581
What about your new job?

1611
01:27:18,624 --> 01:27:20,583
I always liked my old one.

1612
01:27:21,845 --> 01:27:23,281
What's this?

1613
01:27:23,325 --> 01:27:24,326
Photo album.

1614
01:27:25,544 --> 01:27:29,679
I thought we could
start a new one.

1615
01:27:29,722 --> 01:27:32,116
You know I'm a fool
for baby pictures.

1616
01:27:36,076 --> 01:27:38,253
Maddie, your purse!

1617
01:27:38,992 --> 01:27:40,516
Oh, my bag!

1618
01:27:40,559 --> 01:27:42,474
Why don't you check and see
if everything's in there?

1619
01:27:44,607 --> 01:27:45,695
Well, they took my wallet.

1620
01:27:45,738 --> 01:27:46,870
Oh, I'm sorry.

1621
01:27:46,913 --> 01:27:50,177
My keys are here,
my date book, glasses...

1622
01:27:50,961 --> 01:27:53,006
[SIGHS] And my ring.

1623
01:27:58,838 --> 01:28:01,841
I put this ring on your hand
14 years ago.

1624
01:28:04,670 --> 01:28:07,934
Nothing would make me happier
than to have that honor again.

1625
01:28:11,198 --> 01:28:12,983
'Cause,

1626
01:28:13,026 --> 01:28:15,812
Maddie, this man's heart
is still on fire.

1627
01:28:18,423 --> 01:28:19,685
Yes.

1628
01:28:34,091 --> 01:28:35,135
[CLEARS THROAT]

1629
01:28:37,224 --> 01:28:41,098
Our plane leaves
in about five minutes.

1630
01:28:41,141 --> 01:28:43,970
Uh, there has been
a change in plans.

1631
01:28:45,145 --> 01:28:46,146
KIRBY: Dad!

1632
01:28:47,496 --> 01:28:50,455
Ellie, hold this for me,
will you, honey?

1633
01:28:50,499 --> 01:28:52,805
We're gonna start
a new one.

1634
01:28:53,806 --> 01:28:54,981
Let's go home.

1635
01:28:55,025 --> 01:28:57,593
Let's go home!
Come on!

1636
01:28:57,636 --> 01:28:59,943
Ah! We'll sing
Christmas songs.

1637
01:28:59,986 --> 01:29:01,684
KIRBY: Hey, Dad,
can we start a fire?

1638
01:29:01,727 --> 01:29:02,902
MATT: Sure we can.

1639
01:29:02,946 --> 01:29:05,688
So, we'll drink some eggnog?

1640
01:29:05,731 --> 01:29:07,646
KIRBY: I can't wait
for Santa Claus.

1641
01:29:08,517 --> 01:29:10,345
ELLIE: What about grandma?

1642
01:29:10,388 --> 01:29:12,129
MADDIE: We'll call her
from home.

1643
01:29:12,172 --> 01:29:13,957
She can send us
the leftovers.

1644
01:29:14,000 --> 01:29:18,178
KIRBY: Does this mean
we won't have to stencil
angels on toilet paper?

1645
01:29:18,222 --> 01:29:20,050
MADDIE: What are you
talking about?

1646
01:29:21,356 --> 01:29:23,401
ELLIE: I hope
Grandma's not mad.

1647
01:29:23,445 --> 01:29:26,273
MADDIE: Something tells me
she won't mind.

1648
01:29:26,317 --> 01:29:28,406
It's going to be
Christmas as usual.

1649
01:29:28,450 --> 01:29:30,190
[MATT LAUGHS]

1650
01:29:30,234 --> 01:29:32,541
[CHOIR SINGING 
JOY TO THE WORLD]

1651
01:29:32,584 --> 01:29:36,414
♪ And wonders of His love 
And wonders of His love

1652
01:29:36,458 --> 01:29:42,855
♪ And wonders 
Wonders of His love ♪

1653
01:29:44,640 --> 01:29:46,772
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

